<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Common Types of Sponsorship Offerings For Virtual Events</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" src="https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXe6b8KOQl2ft766vHow33vrtsfvuET8SMsaOaptc0d07b6Z-0G6Os7505g8hHYyVLrLVXNjXvBQjU1UQYa3qYDZnWCig73MZmNA_HIChrmtvruYOSYwYgDs0a4N5Zbg-d4WsLmjpnC63JvMvKMcxYdnizcM?key=dO7YXV5NAgh-dcuXLt5jAg" alt=""/></figure>



<p class="has-text-align-center">(Credit: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/value-sponsoring-event-alison-geraghty-o2nkc">Allison Geraghty at Linkedin</a>)</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Company Profile</h3>



<p>Start by showcasing your sponsors prominently. This includes their name, logo, a short description, and links to their social media and website right on your event platform. Highlighting their brand up front and center makes them visible and accessible to all attendees from the get-go.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Downloadable Documents</h3>



<p>Provide a deeper dive into what the sponsor offers through downloadable content like detailed company profiles or product info sheets. This is perfect for sponsors who want to share more about their services or products in a format attendees can save and review later.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Marketing</h3>



<p>Boost your sponsor’s visibility exponentially. Embed their logo on your event’s registration page and include it in all marketing emails. This continuous exposure helps keep the sponsor&#8217;s brand top of mind for all event participants.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Social Media</h3>



<p>Get loud with social media shoutouts. This not only increases the sponsor&#8217;s visibility but also enhances their reach by connecting them with your event’s social media audience. Make sure these shoutouts are creative and frequent to keep the engagement high.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Sponsor Ribbons</h3>



<p>These digital ribbons can be displayed alongside the sponsor’s name on the listing page, giving them an extra layer of distinction. This subtle but effective visual cue helps set sponsors apart from the crowd.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. Live Display Banner Ad</h3>



<p>Keep the sponsor’s brand in constant view with banner ads that run throughout the event sessions. These are perfect for keeping the sponsor’s message front and center, ensuring continuous exposure.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">7. Screening of Logo</h3>



<p>Regularly flash the sponsor’s logo during sessions. This can be a static display or a dynamic appearance during session breaks. It’s a simple yet powerful way to maintain brand presence throughout the event.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">8. Trade Show Booth</h3>



<p>Offer sponsors a virtual booth, where they can interact in real-time or through pre-recorded content with attendees. This can be a game-changer for sponsors looking to simulate a real booth experience with live interactions.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">9. Session Background</h3>



<p>Transform the virtual space with custom backgrounds that feature the sponsor’s branding during presentations. This not only enhances the visual appeal of the session but also embeds the sponsor’s brand into the event’s fabric.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">12 Virtual Event Sponsorship Ideas</h2>



<p>When planning virtual events, incorporating sponsorships in unique and interactive ways not only boosts the visibility of your sponsors but also ramps up the excitement for your attendees. Let&#8217;s walk through some top-tier virtual event sponsorship ideas.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">1. Branded Announcements</h3>



<p>Imagine having the ability to send out real-time notifications that pop up during the event, or even as email and device notifications. For example, picture a pop-up sponsored by &#8220;IBM&#8221; that suddenly announces an impromptu live session on the latest tech innovations. This approach directly introduces the sponsor’s brand to the attendees, making them have stronger brand presence.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">2. Session Sponsorship</h3>



<p>You can allow sponsors to &#8216;own&#8217; a session by displaying their logos prominently alongside the session details and giving them a few minutes at the beginning to engage with the audience directly. For example, Mondelēz International kicks off a discussion on healthy food consumption with a short, compelling intro about their latest healthy snacks. It’s a great way to keep the session dynamic and closely tied to the sponsor’s brand.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">3. Portal Header Sponsor Carousel</h3>



<p>Place a dynamic carousel of sponsor logos at a strategic spot within your event portal, where it&#8217;s always visible. Each logo could link directly to the sponsor’s website. Being featured in a loop that every attendee will see is definitely a way to give the sponsor’s brand constant exposure.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">4. Live Video Booths in Exhibit Halls</h3>



<p>Transform traditional sponsor booths into interactive zones where sponsors can conduct live chats, presentations, or product demos. For instance, &#8220;Penguin Publishers&#8221; might host live sessions with authors, bringing a personal touch to the booth and making it a hot spot for attendee interaction.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">5. Pre-Roll Videos in Sessions</h3>



<p>Before a session starts, why not play a sponsored video? This could be a tutorial from &#8220;Meta&#8221; about a new form of booming content right before a related tech seminar begins. It’s a prime way to keep attendees engaged right from the get-go and build anticipation for the session.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">6. Login Page and Lobby Banners</h3>



<p>Customize the login page with a sponsor’s banner, which is the first thing attendees will see. Similarly, in the event lobby, use a large, eye-catching banner to promote a major sponsor. Picture &#8220;The North Face&#8221; welcoming attendees with a visually striking display featuring their latest outdoor equipment.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">7. Lobby Splash Video</h3>



<p>Positioned right under the lobby banner, a looping splash video can serve multiple purposes, from welcoming attendees to highlighting sponsor messages. Imagine starting the event with a lively video that includes a quick welcome from &#8220;JPMorgan Chase&#8221; sharing useful financial tips—perfect for setting the tone of the event.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">8. Session Stream Watermarks and Lower Thirds</h3>



<p>During your live or pre-recorded sessions, incorporate subtle watermarks or lower third graphics that feature your sponsor’s logo. This could be a discreet yet constant reminder of the sponsor&#8217;s presence, like having &#8220;Zenith Watches&#8221; subtly appear during discussions about time management.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">9. Exhibit/Sponsor Hall Booth Listing</h3>



<p>Create a vibrant, interactive exhibit hall where sponsors can customize their space. Let’s say &#8220;Equity Residential&#8221; showcases their sustainable building solutions through virtual tours and interactive content. This turns a simple booth into an engaging experience that attendees can explore at their leisure.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">10. Gamification Engagement Codes and Prizes</h3>



<p>Inject some fun with gamification elements like codes hidden around your event for attendees to find. You could have &#8220;Tencent&#8221; sponsor this scavenger hunt, offering prizes and making the interaction both fun and rewarding.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">11. Group Networking Rooms</h3>



<p>Set up sponsored networking rooms centered around topics that showcase the sponsors&#8217; expertise. For instance, a room titled &#8220;Exploring AI with OpenAI&#8221; could draw attendees interested in artificial intelligence, positioning the sponsor as a thought leader in the field.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">12. Lobby Social Media Feed</h3>



<p>Integrate a live social media feed into the lobby to feature real-time updates and sponsored posts. This can be a great way to keep the content fresh and engaging while also promoting your sponsors in a dynamic way.</p>



<p>Each of these ideas offers a unique twist on virtual event sponsorship, providing value to sponsors while enhancing the attendee experience. By tailoring these strategies to fit your event and your sponsors&#8217; goals, you create a vibrant, engaging atmosphere that makes your virtual event a memorable one.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Insightful Analytics to Measure Sponsorship Effectiveness</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="732" src="https://micepad.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-6897" srcset="https://micepad.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22.jpeg 1024w, https://micepad.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22-300x214.jpeg 300w, https://micepad.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22-768x549.jpeg 768w, https://micepad.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/image-22-650x465.jpeg 650w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Sponsorship is a key driver in marketing and a part of it is about proving impact. The data you get during the event can provide the sponsorship value, mainly what the sponsors have reaped for sponsoring the event. Use the analytics capability to measure their <a href="https://micepad.co/blog/event-roi" data-type="post" data-id="6733">event ROI</a> impact. </p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Key Data to Provide Sponsors on Measuring Sponsorship ROI</h4>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Number of attendees</li>



<li>Number of leads gathered</li>



<li>Audience behaviour data</li>



<li>How many views for live stream videos</li>



<li>Social media reach</li>



<li>Direct audience engagement: Q&amp;A, Poll</li>



<li>Feedback received</li>
</ul>



<p>There are multiple ways to include sponsorship value in your virtual event experience. Use some of these tips to enhance sponsorship value and show your sponsors how valuable a virtual event can be.&nbsp;</p>



